      "id": "skills-architecture",
      "title": "Skills: Modular Security Capabilities",
      "description": "Each skill lives in its own folder with a logic.py (run function), instruction.md (LLM guidance), and manifest.yaml (metadata). Skills receive shared context (DB, LLM, memory, config) via dependency injection. There are three types: scheduled skills that run on intervals, manual skills triggered on-demand, and the chat_router that orchestrates multi-turn conversations.",
